+# Prompt Templates & Validation Checklist (Reference)
+
+This file contains extended details, modifiers, and validation checklists referenced from the main `SKILL.md` file.
+
+---
+
+## Prompt Modifiers (Extended)
+
+### With Trend Adaptation
+```
+Also read: trend-adapter/SKILL.md
+
+Apply the Trend Adaptation Brief: {trend-brief-filename}
+Use the token overrides and layout modifications specified in the trend brief.
+All brand invariants must still pass — verify after applying overrides.
+```
+
+**When to use:** When the landing page design should follow a specific visual trend (e.g., "Modern SaaS", "Enterprise Trust", or a custom dimension profile).
+
+**Agent behavior:**
+1. Load the Trend Adaptation Brief before generation
+2. Extract the token override sheet and layout modification list
+3. Apply token overrides when building frame/code (replaces base values from `design-tokens/SKILL.md`)
+4. Apply layout modifications to section structure and interaction patterns
+5. Verify all brand invariants still pass after applying overrides
+6. Document which tokens were overridden in the output
+
+### With Variation Selection
+```
+Also read: variation-explorer/SKILL.md
+
+Use Variation Spec: {variation-spec-filename}
+Selected variant: {variant-name} (e.g., "Trust Fortress")
+Follow the section sequence and axis values defined for this variant.
+```
+
+**When to use:** When exploring multiple design variations and you want to lock in a specific variant for execution.
+
+**Agent behavior:**
+1. Load the Variation Spec and locate the selected variant definition
+2. Extract section sequence (which sections appear, in what order)
+3. Extract axis values (e.g., hero height, card style, grid columns)
+4. Build the page using the variant's sequence and axis values
+5. Reference the variant name in Mode C blueprints and Mode A verification reports
+
+### With Both Trend + Variation
+```
+Also read: trend-adapter/SKILL.md, variation-explorer/SKILL.md
+
+Apply Trend Adaptation Brief: {trend-brief-filename}
+Use Variation Spec: {variation-spec-filename}, selected variant: {variant-name}
+Trend overrides take precedence for token values; variant defines page structure.
+```
+
+**When to use:** When both a trend profile and a variation variant should be applied together.
+
+**Precedence rules:**
+1. Variation spec defines page structure (sections, layout)
+2. Trend brief provides token overrides
+3. If a token appears in both variant and trend → use trend value
+4. If a token appears in variant but not trend → use variant value
+5. If a token appears in neither → use base value from `design-tokens/SKILL.md`
+
+### Density Override
+```
+Override density profile: {breathing | standard | comprehensive}
+Adjust section padding and content gap tokens per trend-adapter/SKILL.md Section 2.1.
+```
+
+**When to use:** When you want to adjust overall page density without applying a full trend profile.
+
+**Values:**
+- `breathing` (airy): Increase section padding ~40%, reduce content width slightly
+- `standard`: Use base values from `design-tokens/SKILL.md`
+- `comprehensive` (compact): Reduce section padding ~35%, tighten gutters ~20%
+
+**Agent behavior:** Apply spacing token overrides only; leave color, typography, and interaction patterns unchanged.
+
+### Specific Section Focus
+```
+Generate only the following sections (not full page):
+- Hero section
+- Feature grid section
+- Final CTA section
+Apply all skill file rules to these sections as if building the full page.
+```
+
+**When to use:** When rapid iteration on specific sections, or when testing a component in context without building the entire page.
+
+**Agent behavior:**
+1. Parse brief and select layout as normal
+2. Generate only the listed sections in order
+3. Use consistent styling and tokens as if building the full page
+4. Include assets and self-review checks for the selected sections
+5. Do not generate sections not listed
+
+### With Visual Comparison (Mode B)
+```
+After generating code, push the rendered HTML back into Figma using
+generate_figma_design for side-by-side comparison with the original frame.
+Log any visual discrepancies in the deviation report.
+```
+
+**When to use:** When higher-fidelity comparison between Figma source and generated code is needed.
+
+**Agent behavior:**
+1. Complete all normal Mode B steps (inspect, plan, generate, self-review)
+2. Push generated HTML to Figma via `generate_figma_design`
+3. Visually compare the generated Figma layers against the original frame
+4. Document any spacing, color, typography, or layout discrepancies
+5. Include the visual comparison log in the final report to the user
+
+---
+
+## Validation Checklist (All Modes)
+
+After any execution, the agent self-checks against this list. This is the comprehensive version referenced in `SKILL.md` Section 8.
+
+### Code Output (Modes B and C)
+
+**File Structure:**
+- [ ] Output is exactly 3 files: `index.html`, `styles.css`, `script.js`
+- [ ] All files are in the project output folder (not nested)
+- [ ] No extra files created (no `*.map`, `*.tmp`, etc.)
+
+**HTML Quality:**
+- [ ] All classes use BEM naming with `{product}-` prefix (e.g., `{product}-button`, `{product}-button--primary`)
+- [ ] No inline styles (all styling in CSS)
+- [ ] No hardcoded colors, sizes, or spacing in HTML
+- [ ] Semantic HTML5: `<section>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<nav>`, `<main>` used correctly
+- [ ] All text content from Figma (Mode B) or brief (Mode C) is present — nothing omitted
+- [ ] All images reference `./assets/` paths
+- [ ] Uncertain image mappings have `<!-- TODO -->` comments with description
+- [ ] Heading hierarchy is correct (H1 → H2 → H3, no skips, only one H1 per page)
+- [ ] Alt text on all images (descriptive, not auto-generated)
+- [ ] Form fields (if any) have `<label>` elements with `for` attribute
+
+**CSS Quality:**
+- [ ] All design tokens are CSS custom properties (no hardcoded values in rulesets)
+- [ ] Custom property names follow `--{product}-*` pattern
+- [ ] Variable-bound Figma tokens (Mode B) map to matching custom property names
+- [ ] CSS custom properties defined in `:root` block at top of file
+- [ ] Desktop-first responsive approach (base styles for desktop, media queries for smaller)
+- [ ] Only two responsive breakpoints: `1024px` (tablets) and `480px` (phones)
+- [ ] No hardcoded breakpoints or "magic numbers"
+- [ ] Tinted sections use matched surface/border color pairs from `design-tokens/SKILL.md`
+- [ ] No `!important` unless absolutely necessary (and documented with explanatory comment)
+- [ ] All font sizes, weights, and line-heights reference custom properties
+- [ ] All spacing (padding, margin, gap) references custom properties
+
+**JS Quality:**
+- [ ] jQuery only — no other JS libraries imported
+- [ ] All code wrapped in `$(document).ready()`
+- [ ] Interactive components work correctly: tabs switch, accordions toggle, carousels slide
+- [ ] Scroll behaviors fire at correct thresholds
+- [ ] No console errors or warnings
+- [ ] No inline event handlers (all events bound via jQuery)
+- [ ] IntersectionObserver patterns used for scroll-triggered animations
+- [ ] No hardcoded animation timings (all reference CSS custom properties or constants at top)
+
+**Figma Fidelity (Mode B only):**
+- [ ] Section order matches Figma frame top-to-bottom order
+- [ ] Spacing values match extracted Figma specs (or justified token snap)
+- [ ] Color values match extracted Figma specs (or justified token snap)
+- [ ] Typography (font size, weight, line-height) matches extracted specs
+- [ ] Layout (columns, alignment, gaps) matches Figma structure
+- [ ] Responsive behavior degrades gracefully on mobile (even if Figma only shows desktop)
+
+### Figma Output (Mode A)
+
+**Frame Generation:**
+- [ ] Frame successfully pushed to correct Figma file and page via `use_figma`
+- [ ] Layer naming follows convention from `figma-frame-builder/SKILL.md` Section 4
+- [ ] Every layer has a type prefix (no unnamed or generic layers)
+- [ ] Top-level frame is named `{Product Name} — Landing Page`
+- [ ] Section frames are named `Section: {Type}` (e.g., `Section: Hero`, `Section: Features`)
+- [ ] Component frames are named `{Component Type}: {Label}` (e.g., `Feature Card: Network Monitoring`)
+
+**Design Tokens:**
+- [ ] Design tokens match `design-tokens/SKILL.md` — bound to Figma variables when available
+- [ ] Text colors use `color-text-*` tokens
+- [ ] Background fills use `color-bg-*` and tint pair colors
+- [ ] CTA buttons use `color-primary` token
+- [ ] Spacing uses `space-*` scale and `section-padding-y`
+- [ ] Typography uses `font-heading`, `font-body`, and size/weight/line-height tokens
+- [ ] Shadows use `shadow-*` tokens
+- [ ] Border radius uses `radius-*` tokens
+
+**Design System Reuse:**
+- [ ] Library components searched via `search_design_system` before creating new ones
+- [ ] Existing library components instantiated and reused where possible
+- [ ] Variables bound to frame elements when available (not hardcoded)
+- [ ] Custom components created only when no library match exists
+
+**Content & Accessibility:**
+- [ ] All text content from brief is present — nothing omitted
+- [ ] Content gaps flagged visually (red placeholder text or red-bordered rectangles)
+- [ ] Section order matches selected layout pattern from `layout-patterns/SKILL.md`
+- [ ] Tinted section alternation follows `layout-patterns/SKILL.md` Section 2.2 rules
+- [ ] CTA buttons are visually distinct and sized appropriately
+- [ ] Text contrast sufficient (no light gray on light backgrounds)
+
+**Self-Healing Loop:**
+- [ ] Verification summary included (iterations count, what was fixed)
+- [ ] All visual checks passed or max iterations reached
+- [ ] Deviations logged if any mismatches remain after loop
+- [ ] Screenshot taken and presented to user
+
+### Blueprint Output (Mode C)
+
+**Blueprint File:**
+- [ ] Blueprint saved as `{product}-blueprint.md` in project folder (exact name match)
+- [ ] File uses Markdown format with heading hierarchy
+- [ ] YAML frontmatter not present (blueprints are plain Markdown)
+
+**Blueprint Content:**
+- [ ] All sections from parsed brief are represented in page structure
+- [ ] Component and variant selections reference `component-library/SKILL.md` names exactly
+- [ ] Token values listed match `design-tokens/SKILL.md` (with trend overrides if applicable)
+- [ ] Asset manifest categorizes all images into three types:
+  1. Content images (user-supplied)
+  2. Icons/illustrations (agent generates or user supplies)
+  3. CSS-only graphics (no files needed)
+- [ ] Interaction patterns reference specific `css-js-generator/SKILL.md` sections
+- [ ] Brief filename and generation date recorded
+- [ ] Class prefix and trend/variant profile recorded
+
+**Blueprint Compliance:**
+- [ ] Blueprint matches generated code exactly
+- [ ] Any manual edits to blueprint are reflected in code
+- [ ] Blueprint serves as readable source of truth for future iteration
+
+### General (All Modes)
+
+**Preparation:**
+- [ ] All referenced skill files were read before execution began
+- [ ] Content brief was parsed and sections confirmed before design decisions (Modes A & C)
+- [ ] MCP server connection verified before any Figma operations (Modes A & B)
+- [ ] Figma `/figma-use` skill installed before `use_figma` calls (Modes A & B)
+
+**Design Integrity:**
+- [ ] If trend or variation modifiers were applied, brand invariants still pass
+  - Primary CTA color unchanged
+  - Font families unchanged
+  - Responsive breakpoints unchanged
+  - Output format unchanged
+  - BEM naming unchanged
+- [ ] No deviations from brand identity without explicit user approval
+- [ ] All deviations from expected values are logged and presented to user
+
+**Output Quality:**
+- [ ] Code is production-ready (no placeholders, incomplete code, or debug comments)
+- [ ] Asset paths are correct and follow `./assets/` convention
+- [ ] No sensitive data (API keys, tokens, credentials) in generated files
+- [ ] File sizes are reasonable (no unnecessary duplication or bloat)
+- [ ] All TODO comments are descriptive and actionable
+
+**Communication:**
+- [ ] User is presented with clear summary of what was built
+- [ ] All flagged issues and gaps are explicitly documented
+- [ ] Next steps are clearly explained
+- [ ] Deviation log is provided if any values don't match spec exactly
+
+---
+
+## Common Prompt Patterns
+
+### Iteration Pattern (All Modes)
+
+When iterating after generation:
+
+```
+Read the [blueprint/Figma frame]: {file-reference}
+Read skill files: [list only changed skill files if any, or omit to re-read same]
+
+Apply the following changes:
+- {specific edit 1}
+- {specific edit 2}
+
+Update the [blueprint/frame] and regenerate the affected code files.
+```
+
+**Critical rule:** The agent always reads the blueprint/Figma frame as the current source of truth, not its memory of prior generation.
+
+### Combined Workflow Pattern
+
+When executing multiple modes in sequence:
+
+```
+[Mode A execution]
+[Review/edit Figma]
+
+[Mode B execution pointing to the corrected Figma frame]
+```
+
+Or:
+
+```
+[Mode C execution]
+[Escalate via C → A or C → Figma]
+[Review/edit in Figma]
+[If C → A used, run Mode B; if C → Figma used, may re-run Mode B or C]
+```
+
+### Asset Supply Pattern
+
+When assets are pre-exported:
+
+```
+Pre-exported assets in ./assets/:
+- hero-screenshot.png
+- logo-partners.svg
+- icon-feature-1.svg
+
+Export any remaining assets from Figma that are not in this list.
+```
+
+---
+
+## Error Handling & Recovery
+
+### If MCP Connection Fails (Mode A or B)
+
+```
+Verify remote Figma MCP server is connected: mcp.figma.com/mcp
+Authenticate using the Figma plugin for your agent.
+Re-run the mode prompt after verifying connection.
+```
+
+### If Figma Layer Structure Is Non-Standard
+
+The agent uses visual analysis fallbacks:
+- `get_design_context` structured output for layout
+- Spacing gaps and color changes to infer section boundaries
+- Visual pattern matching for component types
+
+→ See `figma-code-extractor/SKILL.md` Section 7 for full handling rules.
+
+### If Content Brief Has Gaps
+
+Mode A and C flag gaps in red:
+- `[MISSING: {description}]` for missing text
+- `[IMAGE NEEDED: {description}]` for missing images
+
+Agent continues with placeholders; user supplies missing content in iteration.
+
+### If Token Values Don't Match Any Definition
+
+Agent logs as TODO:
+```css
+/* TODO: This value (17px) doesn't match any token in design-tokens/SKILL.md.
+   Closest match: --{product}-space-md. Verify with designer. */
+```
+
+Deviation log is presented to user for review.
